    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## Before you activate this workflow\n\n1. **Gmail account** credential - connect on 'Patient Email Trigger' and 'Create Gmail Draft'.\n2. **Ollama** - this uses raw HTTP Request nodes hitting `http://localhost:11434/api/chat` (no credential needed). If n8n runs in Docker and Ollama runs on the host, change the URL in 'AI Extract Intent' and 'Generate AI Reply' to `http://host.docker.internal:11434/api/chat` (Docker Desktop) or your Ollama container's service name, e.g. `http://ollama:11434/api/chat` (Docker Compose network). Pull the model first: `ollama pull llama3.1`. Change the model name in both nodes if you use a different one.\n3. **Google Calendar account** credential on 'Check Doctor Availability'.\n4. **Google Sheets account** credential + real Sheet ID on 'Update Patient Records'.\n5. **Slack account** credential + real channel names on both Slack nodes.\n6. Edit the doctor->calendar mapping in 'Map Doctor to Calendar'.\n7. Test with 'Execute Workflow' on one email before activating.\n8. Note: unlike OpenAI, Ollama's /api/chat doesn't strictly enforce JSON output even with format:'json' on all models - if 'Parse AI JSON' keeps falling back to defaults, check the raw output of 'AI Extract Intent' and consider a model better at instruction-following (e.g. llama3.1, qwen2.5).",
        "height": 340,
        "width": 460,
        "color": 5
      },
      "id": "setup-notes",
      "name": "Setup Notes",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        220,
        640
      ]
    }
